Ah! You want to know the **predefined (built-in) functions of CodeIgniter 4’s Email library** so you can send emails efficiently. Let’s break them down clearly.

In **CI4**, the Email library (`CodeIgniter\Email\Email`) comes with a rich set of methods you can use out of the box.

---

## **1. Configuration & Initialization**

| Function                                                              | Description                                                         |                                                 |
| --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `initialize(array $config)`                                           | Initialize or override email settings dynamically.                  |                                                 |
| `clear(bool $clearAttachments = false)`                               | Clear email content, headers, and optionally attachments for reuse. |                                                 |
| `setFrom(string $from, string $name = '', string $returnPath = null)` | Set the “From” address and name.                                    |                                                 |
| `setTo(string                                                         | array $to)`                                                         | Set the recipient(s). Can be a string or array. |
| `setCC(string                                                         | array $cc)`                                                         | Set carbon copy recipients.                     |
| `setBCC(string                                                        | array $bcc)`                                                        | Set blind carbon copy recipients.               |
| `setReplyTo(string $email, string $name = '')`                        | Set reply-to email address.                                         |                                                 |

---

## **2. Email Content**

| Function                                                                                                  | Description                                              |
| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| `setSubject(string $subject)`                                                                             | Set email subject.                                       |
| `setMessage(string $body)`                                                                                | Set email body (HTML or plain text based on `mailType`). |
| `attach(string $filePath, string $disposition = 'attachment', string $newName = null, string $mime = '')` | Attach a file to the email.                              |
| `attachContent(string $data, string $filename, string $disposition = 'attachment', string $mime = '')`    | Attach content from a string instead of a file.          |

---

## **3. Sending Emails**

| Function                                                                  | Description                                                    |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `send(bool $autoClear = true)`                                            | Send the email. Returns `true` on success, `false` on failure. |
| `printDebugger(array $include = ['headers', 'subject', 'body', 'debug'])` | Get debug info if sending fails. Useful for troubleshooting.   |
| `sendWithRetry(int $times = 3, int $interval = 2)`                        | Try sending multiple times if fails (CI4.3+).                  |

---

## **4. Helpers & Utility Methods**

| Function             | Description                                        |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `getProtocol()`      | Returns the email protocol (SMTP, mail, sendmail). |
| `getDebugMessages()` | Returns debug messages after sending.              |
| `getSubject()`       | Returns the email subject.                         |
| `getBody()`          | Returns the email body.                            |
| `getFrom()`          | Returns sender info.                               |
| `getRecipients()`    | Returns recipient info.                            |

---

## **5. Example: Full Email with TO, CC, BCC, and Attachment**

```php
$email = \Config\Services::email();

$email->setFrom('your_email@example.com', 'Your Name');
$email->setTo('recipient@example.com');
$email->setCC(['cc1@example.com', 'cc2@example.com']);
$email->setBCC('bcc@example.com');
$email->setReplyTo('replyto@example.com', 'Reply Name');

$email->setSubject('CI4 Predefined Functions Demo');
$email->setMessage('<p>This email demonstrates CI4 built-in email functions.</p>');

// Attach a file
$email->attach('/path/to/file.pdf');

if ($email->send()) {
    echo "Email sent successfully!";
} else {
    echo $email->printDebugger();
}
```

---

✅ **Key Notes:**

* All these functions are **chainable**, so you can write:

```php
$email->setFrom('you@example.com', 'Your Name')
      ->setTo('recipient@example.com')
      ->setSubject('Hello')
      ->setMessage('Test')
      ->send();
```

* You can reuse the email object by calling `$email->clear()` before sending another email.

